30
00:02:07,120 --> 00:02:10,180
We can't go. We're going to dinner. Remember?
摩妮卡和钱德不能去 我们要去吃饭，记得吗？

32
00:02:10,390 --> 00:02:13,950
-Oh,my God. I'm so sorry. -What's the big deal?
-天哪，真抱歉  -干嘛这么激动？

34
00:02:14,730 --> 00:02:19,030
I get mad when Rachel doesn't remember where we're going.
我只是很气瑞秋不记得 我们要去哪里

35
00:02:20,570 --> 00:02:22,330
Where are you going?
你们要去哪里？

36
00:02:24,040 --> 00:02:26,060
-How about you guys? -Open bar?
-那你们呢？ -酒品免费？ 

37
00:02:26,770 --> 00:02:29,740
-I think so. -I can do that for the kids.
-应该是  -我可以为孩子们喝酒

39
00:02:30,810 --> 00:02:35,110
I'll come. I'm making money. It's time I give some back.
那我也要去 我现在有收入 也该回馈社会了

41
00:02:35,320 --> 00:02:38,010
You could give back the money you owe me.
你也可以把欠我的钱还给我

42
00:02:38,990 --> 00:02:41,250
Okay. Have a benefit.
好啊，你办义卖啊

43
00:02:44,190 --> 00:02:47,160
Ross, can you go to a charity event tonight?
罗斯 你晚上可以参加慈善晚会吗？

44
00:02:47,360 --> 00:02:49,300
I have plans with Elizabeth.
不行，我跟伊丽莎白有约

45
00:02:49,500 --> 00:02:52,560
You're already doing your part for the kids.
你已经在为孩童贡献心力了

46
00:02:54,370 --> 00:02:59,030
It's our last night before she leaves for camp. To be a counselor.
再过几天她要去夏令营 去当指导员

48
00:03:00,740 --> 00:03:05,650
I have a question. All jokes aside, where is this relationship going?
罗斯 我问你 撇开笑话不提 这段感情要往哪里走？

50
00:03:05,850 --> 00:03:08,940
All jokes aside? I didn't agree to that.
等等，撇开笑话不提？ 我可不同意

51
00:03:10,390 --> 00:03:13,720
-Do you see this as long-term? -I don't know.
-你认为你们可以长久吗？ -我不知道

52
00:03:13,920 --> 00:03:17,260
-You are 12 years older than her. -Who's counting?
-你比她大12岁喔  -谁会去算？

53
00:03:17,460 --> 00:03:19,890
Well,she is. She's this many.
她会，她才这么大

55
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:24,120
Ross, she is really young.
罗斯，她真的很年轻

56
00:03:24,830 --> 00:03:27,030
Does everyone feel this way?
等等，你们都这么认为吗？

57
00:03:27,470 --> 00:03:29,330
-Yeah,sort of. -Sorry.
有一点 抱歉

58
00:03:30,540 --> 00:03:34,500
I thought you were just making jokes. I had no idea.
我以为你们只是爱开玩笑 我都不知道

59
00:03:34,710 --> 00:03:39,270
You guys are wrong. Yes,there is a chronological age difference.
不过你们都错了 没错，我们是有年龄上的差异

61
00:03:39,480 --> 00:03:43,180
But I never notice it, because she is very mature.
但是我都感觉不到 为什么？因为她很成熟

62
00:03:43,380 --> 00:03:48,120
It doesn't matter what you guys think. I'm dating Elizabeth, not you.
况且我根本不在意你们的看法 跟她交往的是我，不是你们

64
00:03:48,320 --> 00:03:50,660
Not what she said last night.
她昨晚可不是这么说的

65
00:03:52,690 --> 00:03:54,660
See,now,he could date her.
他配她就够幼稚

66
00:03:59,400 --> 00:04:01,100
Will you marry me?
你愿意嫁给我吗？

67
00:04:02,300 --> 00:04:04,170
Will you marry me?
你愿意嫁给我吗？

68
00:04:04,370 --> 00:04:06,170
Hey, you marry me.
嫁给我

69
00:04:13,620 --> 00:04:18,450
-What's going on, little elves? -It's the big night. We wish you luck.
-怎么了，小精灵们？ -今晚很重要，我们想祝你好运

71
00:04:18,650 --> 00:04:20,920
-You have the ring? -In my pocket.
戒指带了吗？ 就在口袋里

72
00:04:26,230 --> 00:04:27,890
-Phoebe. -Wha..?
菲比

73
00:04:30,530 --> 00:04:34,430
Will you guys get out of here? This is a surprise.
麻烦你们出去 我想给她惊喜，她会看出来

74
00:04:34,640 --> 00:04:37,230
Yeah,you guys. Get out of here.
没错，快出去

75
00:04:39,270 --> 00:04:40,830
Hey,guys.
你们好

76
00:04:42,980 --> 00:04:46,280
-You look beautiful. -Thank you.
-你好漂亮 -谢谢

78
00:04:52,290 --> 00:04:53,980
What's going on?
怎么了？

79
00:04:54,190 --> 00:04:56,050
We're just really...
我们只是… 

80
00:04:56,260 --> 00:04:59,920
excited about this charity event we have to go to.
要参加慈善晚会觉得很兴奋

81
00:05:05,200 --> 00:05:06,760
-Here. -Thank you.
给你 谢谢

82
00:05:06,970 --> 00:05:11,270
-So, what's going on here? -Well,this is a silent auction.
-现在是怎样？ -这是一场不喊价拍卖会

84
00:05:11,470 --> 00:05:14,960
They lay the stuff here. You write down your offer.
要卖的东西都在这里 你写下竞标价

85
00:05:15,180 --> 00:05:17,240
Then the highest bid gets it.
出价最高的就是得主

86
00:05:17,450 --> 00:05:21,940
I know what a silent auction is. What's going on with your hair?
我知道什么叫不喊价拍卖会 我是说你的头发怎么了？

88
00:05:23,690 --> 00:05:26,380
-Why? -No,it's nice.
-怎么说？ -不是啊，很好看

90
00:05:27,890 --> 00:05:31,050
Nice to see you. So glad you brought someone.
欢迎 你带了一位朋友来

91
00:05:31,260 --> 00:05:33,060
Someone? I brought people.
一位？我带了两位 

92
00:05:33,260 --> 00:05:37,820
Phoebe, this is Mr. Thompson. He's the head of my department.
菲比，这位是汤普森先生 他是我的部门主管

94
00:05:38,030 --> 00:05:41,900
-And I also brought my friend Joey. -Shrimp toast!
-我还带了我的朋友乔伊… -虾子吐司

96
00:05:43,170 --> 00:05:46,270
You know, I don't know where he is.
我不知道他在哪里

97
00:05:47,040 --> 00:05:48,600
I hope you'll bid.
希望你会参加竞标

98
00:05:48,810 --> 00:05:52,800
Actually,I was about to bid on this lovely trip to Paris.
我正打算投标这趟巴黎之旅

99
00:05:53,010 --> 00:05:56,310
-Nice choice. Good luck. -Thank you.
-有眼光，祝你好运  -谢谢

100
00:05:57,620 --> 00:05:58,610
Okay.
好

101
00:05:58,820 --> 00:06:01,220
Twenty dollars.
20元

102
00:06:09,260 --> 00:06:11,730
Shut the door! Shut the door!
把门关上，把门关上

103
00:06:12,000 --> 00:06:15,630
-What's going on? -Guys are throwing water balloons.
-怎么了？ -对面的男生在朝我们丢水球

105
00:06:15,800 --> 00:06:19,640
Call the cops. That's what I did to kids in my building.
你们得报警 我都这样对付我家那栋的小孩

106
00:06:19,840 --> 00:06:23,570
No, it's a water balloon fight. We started it.
这是水球仗，是我们挑起的

107
00:06:25,010 --> 00:06:29,240
I stopped by to see if you wanted to see this play tonight.
听我说 我来问你晚上要不要去看戏

108
00:06:29,450 --> 00:06:31,750
It's excellent. The director is..
这出戏应该很棒，导演…

109
00:06:31,950 --> 00:06:35,890
-Who drank all the kamikazes? -Nobody. We put them in here!
-谁把神风特攻队都喝了？ -没有，在水球里

111
00:06:36,720 --> 00:06:38,280
You want some?
你要吗？ 不要

112
00:06:40,190 --> 00:06:44,390
-Could I talk to you for a second? -Yeah,sure.
我可以跟你讲一下话吗？ 当然可以

113
00:06:44,600 --> 00:06:46,970
So this play, what do you think?
所以你要去看戏吗？ 

115
00:06:47,170 --> 00:06:50,000
-It's gotten great reviews.. -Attack!
-它的剧评很好…  -攻击！

117
00:06:52,210 --> 00:06:55,700
-Put your balloons down! -You put your balloons down!
-放下水球 -你们才放下

118
00:06:55,910 --> 00:07:00,440
Everybody put their balloons down!
统统都把水球放下

120
00:07:02,350 --> 00:07:05,550
Now,this is a nice suit!
这可是高级西装

121
00:07:09,620 --> 00:07:11,180
If you'll excuse us...
请你们出去一下 

122
00:07:11,360 --> 00:07:15,850
I would like to speak to Elizabeth alone for a moment.
我要单独跟伊丽莎白谈谈

123
00:07:18,570 --> 00:07:21,500
Whoa,Liz. Your dad's a bummer.
丽莎，你爸好扫兴

124
00:07:24,710 --> 00:07:28,200
Our next item is the romantic trip to Paris.
下一项拍卖品是巴黎浪漫之旅

125
00:07:28,410 --> 00:07:33,040
It goes to Emil Alexander with a high bid of $2300.
由艾弥尔亚历山大 以2千3百元的高价得标

126
00:07:33,210 --> 00:07:35,380
So close!
只差一点

127
00:07:36,880 --> 00:07:39,250
Guys,look. Got me some drinks.
你们看，我拿了几杯酒

128
00:07:41,060 --> 00:07:44,420
-What are you doing? -Open bar.
-你在干什么？ -不用钱嘛

129
00:07:45,330 --> 00:07:47,820
Well,now it's an empty bar.
你会把人家喝垮

130
00:07:48,630 --> 00:07:52,790
You can't stand anyone else enjoying themselves, can you?
你就是见不得别人开心对吧？

131
00:07:53,000 --> 00:07:54,990
Finally,our biggest item.
最后是今晚的最大项目

132
00:07:55,400 --> 00:07:58,700
The 22-foot Gentleman's Daysailer sailboat.
22尺豪华帆船

133
00:07:58,910 --> 00:08:02,570
The winning bid was a whopping $20,000.
得标金额高达2万元

134
00:08:03,810 --> 00:08:05,400
I won.
我赢了

135
00:08:06,950 --> 00:08:08,880
That was my guess.
那是我猜的

136
00:08:09,880 --> 00:08:13,290
-What? What? What? -I guessed $20,000.
-什么？ -我猜2万

137
00:08:13,690 --> 00:08:17,590
Joey,it is an auction. You don't guess. You buy!
乔伊，这是拍卖会 你不是猜，是买

138
00:08:18,860 --> 00:08:20,160
What?
什么？

139
00:08:22,230 --> 00:08:23,660
I don't have $20,000.
我没有2万

140
00:08:23,870 --> 00:08:27,730
Congratulations on your new boat, Joey Tribbiani.
恭喜你购得新船… 乔伊崔比亚尼

141
00:08:31,110 --> 00:08:32,600
Joey,sit down.
坐下啦

142
00:08:33,310 --> 00:08:36,070
Forget her. You enjoy this.
别理她，开心就好

143
00:08:53,460 --> 00:08:55,020
What are you doing?
你在干什么？

144
00:08:55,760 --> 00:08:57,360
"One nation...
一个国家

145
00:08:58,270 --> 00:09:02,970
under God,indivisible, with liberty and justice for all."
在神之下 不可分割，全民拥有 自由公正

147
00:09:03,640 --> 00:09:06,330
I remembered it. The champagne is here.
我记得是这样背，香槟来了

148
00:09:07,280 --> 00:09:10,010
-You okay? -Yes. I'm good. Are you good?
-你没事吧？ -我很好，你好吗？ 

150
00:09:10,210 --> 00:09:12,650
Is everything..? Are you perfect?
这一切…你很好吗？

151
00:09:13,350 --> 00:09:14,540
Yeah. I'm okay.
还好

152
00:09:14,750 --> 00:09:18,050
Actually,I'm a bit cold. Can I have your jacket?
其实我有点冷 外套可以借我吗？

154
00:09:18,520 --> 00:09:21,320
No, you can't have my jacket.
不行，我的外套不能借你

155
00:09:22,120 --> 00:09:24,460
Because then I would be cold.
因为那样我就会冷

156
00:09:24,860 --> 00:09:29,020
If you thought you'd be cold, you should've brought a jacket.
你要是觉得会冷 应该自己带外套

157
00:09:30,130 --> 00:09:33,260
But, other than that, are you okay?
除此之外你好吗？

158
00:09:34,470 --> 00:09:38,840
-Are you sure you're okay? -Yes. I'm fine.
-你真的没事吗？ -对，我很好

160
00:09:39,040 --> 00:09:44,240
In fact,I've been fine for a long time now and I think...
我这段日子一直都很好 我觉得…

161
00:09:44,450 --> 00:09:46,380
the reason is you.
都是因为有你

162
00:09:47,280 --> 00:09:48,310
That's sweet.
好甜蜜喔

164
00:09:52,290 --> 00:09:56,090
Before I met you, I had really little life.
认识你之前 我的人生微不足道

165
00:09:57,660 --> 00:10:01,060
-And I couldn't imagine growing old.. -Oh,my God.
-我无法想像一个人… -我的天哪 

166
00:10:01,260 --> 00:10:03,890
-I know. But let me say it. -Richard.
-我知道，不过让我说完  -理查

167
00:10:04,230 --> 00:10:06,430
What? I'm Chandler.
什么？我是钱德

169
00:10:08,700 --> 00:10:10,260
Oh, that's Richard.
那是理查

170
00:10:11,670 --> 00:10:14,470
Maybe he won't see us. Richard!
也许他会没看见 理查

171
00:10:18,850 --> 00:10:20,810
Monica. Chandler.
摩妮卡，钱德

172
00:10:23,520 --> 00:10:25,610
I don't know why I did that.
我不知道我为什么要抱你

173
00:10:26,690 --> 00:10:30,020
-Good to see you. -You too. You let your hair grow.
-见到你真好 -彼此彼此，你把头发留长了

175
00:10:30,220 --> 00:10:32,950
That's right. You always wanted me to.
没错，你一直希望我留长

176
00:10:33,160 --> 00:10:37,120
-I see your mustache is back. -Well,my nose got lonely.
-你又开始留胡子了 -我的鼻子感到寂寞

178
00:10:37,500 --> 00:10:40,430
You don't have a mustache, which is good.
你没留胡子，很好

179
00:10:42,470 --> 00:10:45,630
Chandler. I make jokes when I'm uncomfortable.
我是钱德，我一蹩扭就开玩笑

180
00:10:46,170 --> 00:10:47,970
-Hi,I'm Lisa. -Hi.
我是丽莎

181
00:10:48,180 --> 00:10:52,910
I'm sorry. Lisa, Monica, Chandler. We used to date.
抱歉，丽莎 摩妮卡，钱德 我们交往过

183
00:10:53,110 --> 00:10:56,680
Richard, no one's supposed to know about us.
理查，我们的事应该保密

184
00:10:58,790 --> 00:11:00,750
See? I did it again.
我又来了

185
00:11:01,860 --> 00:11:04,590
-Chandler,sit down. -I'll sit down.
-钱德，我们坐下吧 -好，我坐

186
00:11:04,790 --> 00:11:07,590
-Good to see you. -Your table's ready,sir.
-很高兴见到你  -您的桌子准备好了

188
00:11:07,800 --> 00:11:09,320
Good to see you guys.
很高兴遇见你们 

189
00:11:09,500 --> 00:11:12,130
If you prefer,this table's available.
这一桌也是空的

190
00:11:13,070 --> 00:11:14,830
That might be fun.
一起坐应该不错

191
00:11:21,540 --> 00:11:25,380
-What were you thinking? -I didn't know it was an auction.
你在想什么？ 我不知道这是拍卖会

193
00:11:25,580 --> 00:11:30,020
I figured I'd take a guess. Help a charity. Free boat!
我以为是猜一猜 帮助慈善团体，免费得帆船

194
00:11:30,690 --> 00:11:33,350
Why would a charity give away a boat?
慈善团体为什么要送帆船？

195
00:11:33,550 --> 00:11:36,520
I don't know. Charity?
我哪知，做慈善吗？

196
00:11:37,430 --> 00:11:39,950
Well,just buy the damn boat.
你就买吧

197
00:11:40,830 --> 00:11:43,700
Don't you think you've had enough to drink?
菲比，你喝得够多了吧？

198
00:11:43,860 --> 00:11:46,130
I'm just helping the kids.
我只是在帮助儿童

199
00:11:47,300 --> 00:11:49,860
How is you drinking helping the kids?
你喝酒怎么能帮助儿童？

200
00:11:50,070 --> 00:11:54,800
Because the more I drink, the less there is for the kids to drink.
我喝得越多 孩子们能喝的就越少

201
00:11:58,210 --> 00:12:01,110
Mr. Tribbiani, your contribution brings us...
崔比亚尼先生 你的慷慨解囊 

202
00:12:01,320 --> 00:12:04,440
a step closer to building the youth center.
让兴建活动中心的事大有进展

203
00:12:04,650 --> 00:12:08,590
-I'm so happy you brought him. -So am I.
-我很高兴你带他来 -我也是

204
00:12:08,790 --> 00:12:11,820
